			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">druids have the largeste playerbase in the game.  Its a matter of more people yelling = louder noise.
<br />

<br />
We don't have that luxury.  
<br />

<br />
Pets need to be fixed, but this is not the way it should be done.  Frankly, I agree with the other suggestion of cloning mage stats with modifiers.  The only thing that i didn't agree with the earlier post on was the damage.  Damage that pets do quite simply has to be ramped up by a large degree.  When  i was a level 50 mage before any of the expansions, i had the best sustained damage in the game.  None of this 700dps rogue crap I've been hearing about lately.  I have a very very very simple solution to all of the problems we've been having.
<br />

<br />
When the mage dings 61, 1.5X dmg modifier on current pet max dmg.  When mage dings 63, 2X dmg modifier on current pet max dmg.  When mage dings 65, 3X dmg, maybe 4X damage on dinging 70.
<br />

<br />
Is it a perfect solution? nope.  Does it work? yup.
<br />

<br />
Here's why.
<br />

<br />
if a pet is churning out say 80dps right now, your average 65 mage pet will be churning out 240dps, adding 160dps to mages.  Thats a nice boost.    
<br />

<br />
Now lets look at a time geared mage.  We're using the mage to clone stats so an uber mage with maxed out stats  now has a pet that has a significantly higher atk, AC and HP than the pet of a bazaar 65 mage.  This means that their DPS as well as mitigating ability is going to be significantly ramped up.
<br />

<br />
So, what does this mean to your average mage?
<br />

<br />
==>  approx 160-200 dps boost.  This IS ACCEPTABLE FOR THE AVERAGE MAGE.  It brings us back in line. (indicently, about 240-280 dps boost at level 70)
<br />

<br />
What does it mean to uber mages?
<br />

<br />
==> Tougher to say, but upwards of 250-300 dps boost.  (maybe 400-450 dps boost with OOW)  This is significantly higher than bazaar mages, and puts mages back on top of the sustatained DPS list.
<br />

<br />
Now before people say this is overpowered, stop and think for a second.  With the state of the game, the HP of the mobs etc, is our pets hitting for upwards of 500dmg at level 70 overpowering?
<br />

<br />
The answer is no.  People will bitch that we've gotten  such a huge power boost, but ultimately, it will help everyone. 
<br />

<br />
Oh and before you ask, half those stats for BL and necro.  1.25 at 61, 1.5 mod at 63, 2.0 mod at 65 and 2.5 mod at 70.  In terms of pet dps this very clearly seperates the classes into 3 distinct tiers: 1) Mage, 2) BL, 3) necro.  This is the way i believe that it should be.
<br />

<br />
AND GIVE ME VOICE GRAFT!<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">It is known that there are an infinite number of worlds, simply because there is an infinite amount of space for them to be in.  However, not every one of them is inhabited.  Therefore, there must be a finite number of inhabited worlds.  Any finite number divided by infinity is as near to nothing, so the average population of all the planets in the Universe can be said to be zero.  From this it follows that the population of the whole Universe is also zero, and that any people you may meet from time to time are merely the products of a deranged imagination.</span>  Douglas Adams</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
